    "index_reference": "talmai",
    "language": "eng",
    "content": "<h1>TALMAI</h1><ol><li><p>A son of Anak and brother of Ahiman and Sheshai. The 12 Israelite spies saw Talmai and his people when they explored the land of Canaan (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:22\">Numbers 13:22</a>). Later, Caleb was successful in defeating Talmai and his brothers. They were living in Hebron (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:14\">Joshua 15:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:10\">Judges 1:10</a>).</p></li><li><p>A son of Ammihud and father of Maacah. Maacah was the wife of King David. She gave birth to Absalom, the third son of David (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:3\">2&nbsp;Samuel 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr3:2\">1&nbsp;Chronicles 3:2</a>). After Absalom killed his half-brother Amnon, he ran away to his grandfather Talmai&apos;s small kingdom of Geshur for safety. (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam13:37\">2&nbsp;Samuel 13:37</a>).</p></li></ol>",
